# Build context = repo root. The image bundles the SELF-CONTAINED engine:
# src/ (code + web/ viewer & vendored assets + templates/ skeletons) and
# requirements.txt. The content (the "mind") arrives at runtime via git clone
# into /app/repo — NOT via the image. So everything else is excluded: a minimal
# context, and above all .git (whose .git/config may hold the GitHub PAT) kept
# out of the image.
*
!src
!requirements.txt
